olive oil
½ Onion
1 cucumber
½ packet cherry tomatoes
½ lemon
1 packet Venison & Beef Mince
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 packet Currants
1 packet fine breadcrumbs
1 egg
½ tbs white wine vinegar
2 Burger Bun
½ packet Cow's Milk Feta
1 packet Italian Truffle Mayonnaise
1 packet Mixed Salad Leaves

• Thinly slice onion (see ingredients).
• Slice cucumber(see ingredients) into half-moons. Halve cherry tomatoes.
• Slice lemon into wedges.
• In a large bowl, combine venison & beef mince, garlic & herb seasoning, currants, fine breadcrumbs and the egg. Using damp hands, shape mince mixture into 2cm-thick patties (1 per person).

• In a small microwave-safe bowl, combine onion, the white wine vinegar and a good pinch of sugar and salt.
• Microwave onion, until softened, for 30 seconds.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook venison-beef patties until just cooked through, 4-5 minutes each side (cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded).
• Meanwhile, halve, then toast or grill burger buns to your liking.
• Drain pickled onions.
• In a large bowl, combine cucumber, cherry tomatoes, cow's milk feta (see ingredients), a generous squeeze of lemon juice, half the pickled onion and a drizzle of olive oil. Season to taste

• Spread some Italian truffle mayonnaise over the burger bun bases.
• Top with a Mediterranean venison and beef patty, the remaining pickled onion and mixed salad leaves.
• Serve with feta chopped salad. Enjoy!